Hi David,

I am adding user profile synchronization to a Quartz Job so I dealed 
with some of your problems. This is what I did in order to successfuly 
create/update the user profile:

1. You need to dynamicaly load "SakaiPersonManager" and 
"AgentGroupManager" like the example below:
public SakaiPersonManager getSakaiPersonManager() {
if(sakaiPersonManager == null){
sakaiPersonManager = (SakaiPersonManager) 
ComponentManager.get(SakaiPersonManager.class.getName());
}
return sakaiPersonManager;
}
public AgentGroupManager getAgentGroupManager() {
if(agentGroupManager == null){
agentGroupManager = (AgentGroupManager) 
ComponentManager.get(AgentGroupManager.class.getName());
}
return agentGroupManager;
}


2. The profile corresponds to the sakai db table SAKAI_PERSON_T which 
have as primary keys agent_uuid and type_uuid. From what I have seen, 
this type used was always UserMutableType (even the admin user) - you 
will need to switch the session to the user you're modifying (method 
setSakaiSessionUser()). You can get existing/create new profile like this:
private SakaiPerson getUserProfile(String userId, String type) {
SakaiPersonManager spm = getSakaiPersonManager();
Agent agent = null;
try{
agent = 
getAgentGroupManager().getAgentBySessionManagerUserId(userId);
}catch(Exception e1){
LOG.error("Failed to update profile for user " + userId + ": 
" + e1.getMessage());
return null;
}
setSakaiSessionUser(userId); // switch to that user's session
Type _type = spm.getUserMutableType();
SakaiPerson sakaiPerson = null;
if(agent != null){
try{
sakaiPerson = spm.getSakaiPerson(userId, _type);
// create profile if it doesn't exist
if(sakaiPerson == null){
sakaiPerson = spm.create(userId, userId, _type);
}
}catch(Exception e){
LOG.error("Unknown error occurred in getUserProfile(" + 
userId + "): " + e.getMessage());
e.printStackTrace();
}
}
return sakaiPerson;
}
private synchronized void setSakaiSessionUser(String id) {
Session sakaiSession = SessionManager.getCurrentSession();
sakaiSession.setUserId(id);
sakaiSession.setUserEid(id);
}


3. After retrieving the SakaiPerson object, you can edit its properties 
and save to the database with the API. You can then switch back to the 
admin session:
private void updateUserProfile(String userId, String firstName, 
String lastName, String email, String dept, byte[] jpegPhoto, String type) {
if(userId == null || userId.equals("")){
LOG.error("Failed to update profile for user: (null or 
empty).");
return;
}
SakaiPerson sakaiPerson = getUserProfile(userId, type);
if(sakaiPerson != null){
try{
sakaiPerson.setJpegPhoto(jpegPhoto);
sakaiPerson.setSystemPicturePreferred(Boolean.TRUE);
sakaiPerson.setGivenName(firstName);
sakaiPerson.setSurname(lastName);
sakaiPerson.setDisplayName(firstName + " " + lastName);
sakaiPerson.setMail(email);
sakaiPerson.setCampus("Universidade Fernando Pessoa");
sakaiPerson.setDepartmentNumber(dept);
getSakaiPersonManager().save(sakaiPerson);
profilesUpdated++;
setSakaiSessionUser("admin");  // get back the admin session
}catch(IllegalAccessError e){
LOG.error("Failed to update profile for user " + userId 
+ " - no permissions: " + e.getMessage());
}catch(Exception e){
LOG.error("Failed to update profile for user " + userId 
+ ": " + e.getMessage());
e.printStackTrace();
}
}
}


I hope that it helps!
Nuno Fernandes.



